snippet.textDisplay:
Little bit of background on the song:

Kate is a white woman married into the Royal Family to William. Meghan is a black woman married into the Royal Family to Harry. She was slandered from day dot out of racism and it was very much frowned upon that a black American was being married into the Royal Family. Harry and Meghan have dropped their Royal status and are now leading a different life.

Grenfell victims were promised accommodation from when their homes burned down due to them being built with dangerous materials and they STILL have not got accommodation. It happened in 2017 and took the lives of almost 100 people.

Verse 2 speaks of the danger most black kids grow up in the UK. Usually they have to join gangs or start dealing to keep up the money etc etc and talks about the hardships black families have to go through to survive.

And then lastly the fact black men are condemned for speaking the truth. While white men are rewarded with fake justice.

Other than that I believe everything you understand but that shit with Meghan happened recently and Grenfell was 3 years ago.

-Written from Northern Ireland.
